benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: Valid GET coverage: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05 demonstrate successful retrieval with valid parameters and audit controls.
Empty response handling: TC06 covers returning an empty array when no matches are found.
Pagination coverage: TC02, TC07 (limit/offset), TC09 (offset beyond range), and TC28 (pagination with audit) validate paging behavior for large/result sets.

Query parameters validation: TC02 (limit/offset), TC11 (malformed limit), TC12 (negative limit), TC13 (negative offset), TC14 (invalid audit), TC10 (ignore unsupported params), TC28 (audit with pagination), TC29 (defaults), TC18/TC27 (input validation with special/Unicode), TC25 (whitespace/unusual input).
Authorization checks: TC15 (missing token) and TC16 (invalid token) verify authentication handling.
Error handling coverage: 400 responses for invalid inputs (TC11–TC14), 401 for auth issues (TC15, TC16), 503 for service unavailability (TC17), and 405 for wrong HTTP method (TC30).
Security considerations: TC18 (XSS/injection attempt) and TC27 (Unicode) address input sanitization and security.
Performance/concurrency coverage: TC19 (stress test) and TC20 (concurrent requests) address performance and race-condition concerns.

Compatibility/regression: TC21 (empty searchKey behavior), TC22 (legacy path), TC24 (documentation/error messaging), TC28 (audit with pagination), TC29 (default param set), TC23 (integration/data consistency).
Documentation/accessibility: TC24 validates descriptive/error messaging and API docs alignment.
gaps: Rate limiting tests: no scenarios validating throttling or rate-limit enforcement (e.g., 429 responses).
Caching behavior: no tests verifying caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) or 304 responses.
Authorization edge-case: no explicit test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient privileges.
Additional 5xx coverage beyond 503/service unavailability (e.g., 500 Internal Server Error) is not addressed via GET tests.
recommendations: Add a dedicated 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient privileges, separate from 401 authentication failures.
Introduce tests that validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and behavior on subsequent requests (e.g., 304 Not Modified).
Add rate-limiting/concurrency specificity tests (e.g., multiple rapid requests) and expect appropriate 429 or related behavior if enforced.
Refactor test suite with a Scenario Outline or Examples table to consolidate parameterized GET tests (limit, offset, audit, searchKey) to reduce duplication.
Consider adding a dedicated 500 Internal Server Error scenario for GET to ensure proper handling when backend/unexpected failures occur.
